The paper presents a novel technique for program repair, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE). The approach involves statistical correlation analysis and pattern-matching based synthesis, which could also be categorized under programming languages (cs.PL) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The user study and application to a Unix utility program suggest a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and systems and control (cs.SY) as well.
